On Sun, 30 Jun 2002, Greg Potts wrote:

> While the curtains are off the door I am considering putting an interior
> hatch release and fitting a handle to pull it shut with. If anyone has done
> this before please let me know what has worked for you.

78 and it was crude, cut about a 1x1 inch hole in the panel just to the
right of the latch and just about an inch or so above the metal,  ran a
heavy duty wire tie around an already provided release lever,  like I
said crude but it works

